==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Floccillation
<hw>Floc`cil*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>floccus</ets> a flock of wool. Cf. <er>Flock</er> of wool.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A delirious picking of bedclothes by a sick
person, as if to pick off flocks of wool; carphology; -- an alarming
symptom in acute diseases.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Floccose</ent>⟦br⟧
